#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enable this option, &kfind; will only find text in files with the "
"exact case matching, &eg; <userinput>MARC</userinput> will only match "
"<quote>MARC</quote>, not <quote>Marc</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Įjungus šią parinktį, &kfind; ras tik tokius failus, kurių viduje bus "
"nurodytas tekstas, parašytas lygiai tokio paties dydžio raidėmis, t.y. "
"<userinput>MARGIS</userinput> ras tik <quote>MARGIS</quote>, bet ne "
"<quote>Margis</quote>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regular expression"
msgstr "Įprastoji išraiška"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have installed the &kregexpeditor; tool from playground/utils on "
#| "the &kde; svn server, you will have this additional option. Enabling it "
#| "will allow you to search for a <firstterm>regexp</firstterm> or regular "
#| "expression. A regexp is a way to specify conditions for your search, and "
#| "they can be very complex, and equally they can be very powerful. If you "
#| "are unfamiliar with regular expressions, you can choose <guibutton>Edit</"
#| "guibutton> button to open &kregexpeditor;. This tool allows you to "
#| "construct your set of conditions graphically, and then generates the "
#| "expression for you."
msgid ""
"If you have installed the &kregexpeditor; tool from playground/utils on the "
"&kde; git server, you will have this additional option. Enabling it will "
"allow you to search for a <firstterm>regexp</firstterm> or regular "
"expression. A regexp is a way to specify conditions for your search, and "
"they can be very complex, and equally they can be very powerful. If you are "
"unfamiliar with regular expressions, you can choose <guibutton>Edit</"
"guibutton> button to open &kregexpeditor;. This tool allows you to construct "
"your set of conditions graphically, and then generates the expression for "
"you."
msgstr ""
"Ši parinktis bus rodoma tik tada, jei įdiegėte &kregexpeditor;. Įjungus ją "
"galėsite ieškoti nurodydami <firstterm>regexp</firstterm> – įprastąją "
"išraišką. Regexp – labai lankstus bei galingas (todėl kartais labai "
"sudėtingas) būdas nurodyti paieškos kriterijus. Jei nesate detaliai "
"susipažinę su regexp, galite spausti mygtuką <guibutton>Redaguoti</"
"guibutton> ir tada bus atvertas &kregexpeditor;. Šio įrankio pagalba "
"galėsite grafiškai sukonstruoti regexp sąlygas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kregexpeditor; is a very useful tool, and can be used from within many "
"&kde; applications other than &kfind;. You can find more information from "
"within its own help file."
msgstr ""
"&kregexpeditor; – labai naudingas įrankis, iškviečiamas iš bet kokios &kde; "
"programos (t.y. ne tik iš &kfind;). Daugiau informacijos apie šį įrankį "
"rasite jo paties vadove."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include binary files"
msgstr "Įskaityti dvejetainius failus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This lets you search in any type of file, even those that usually do not "
"contain text (for example program files and images)."
msgstr ""
"Leidžia ieškoti bet kokio tipo failuose, net ir tuose, kuriuose paprastai "
"nebūna teksto (pavzydžiui programų ar piešinių failuose)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search metainfo sections"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These two fields can be used to search within files' specific comments or "
"metainfo."
